This Is Not Tina
BSAI——人工智能学士学位的诞生

在今天的知乎专栏里，我想全球首发一份BSAI的中文新闻稿。英文稿链接：Carnegie Mellon School of Computer Science中文稿夹杂了很多私货，做了很多用心解读 。除了我就要成为CMU校友这一事实之外，并无利益冲突，特此说明。人工智能学士学位的诞生，在AI如日中天的当下可以说是众望所归。这对我来说也有特殊的意义，毫不夸张地说，十年前我就在期待它的诞生了。讲真，我是在懵懵懂懂念到本科最后一年才忽然顿悟，什么才是我在大学时代最想要的知识体系。当时选课相对比较自由，除了必修课之外我基本随兴趣选、也参加过一些不计入学分的通识课程。总的来说，修过的课里让我最着迷的非认知科学莫属。那是我第一次在一门课中，同时接触到认知心理学、哲学、语言学、计算机科学、神经科学等诸多角度对智能（intelligence）本源、模拟及相应伦理的探讨，大呼过瘾！十年后，这个本科学位终于在卡内基·梅隆大学（Carnegie Mellon University, CMU）诞生了。美国首个人工智能学士学位开设在这里，可能是向传统致敬的最好方式。——————————————————————————————人工智能的发源地CMU见证了AI早期黄金时代的六十年代。总是听心理系的老一辈教授们提当年这里的往事。其中，不得不提到的两位便是信息处理语言（Information Processing Language，IPL）的发明者们，赫伯特·西蒙（Herbert Simon）与 艾伦·纽厄尔（Allen Newell）。在1956年，他们合写了"逻辑理论家"（Logic Theorist）和"一般问题解决器"（General Problem Solver）。这是世界上公认最早的AI程序。对人工智能发展史好奇的你可以戳这里了解更多： Timeline of artificial intelligence​en.wikipedia.org（插一句，当今老有微信公众号动不动就夸谁谁是跨界大神、跨界通才，本座实在是看不下去。你们先了解一下赫伯特·西蒙的辉煌历史再考虑要不要使用"跨界大神"一词好吗？现代科学的发展趋向复杂性和系统性，能在某个学科或领域独树一帜已然不易。而西蒙当年在计算机、心理学、管理学、经济学等不同领域轻松拿到10项业内最高成就奖，包括诺贝尔经济学奖、计算机图灵奖、美国心理学会终身成就奖、美国国家科学奖。这才是真跨界大神。）http://www.cs.cmu.edu/simon/​www.cs.cmu.eduHerbert A. Simon TributeHerbert A. Simon Tribute​www.cs.cmu.edu传奇暑校转眼时间切换到1986年，CMU迎来了第一界 Connectionist Summer School。下面这张照片很珍贵，当下AI的时代弄潮儿们几乎都在这张照片中有所出现。借用 @Yuanning 说过的一句话，”所有玩神经网络、计算神经、计算语言的后辈们，几乎都能在这张照片里找到自家的祖师爷！（Y. Li, personal communication）" (哇塞，我这个引用做得好学术好专业呀，求表扬！)图片来源：1986 Connectionist Models Summer School, CMU官方注释：This is the official picture taken at the first Connectionist Models Summer School organized by Geoff Hinton, Terry Sejnowski and Dave Rumelhart at Carnegie-Mellon University in July 1986.Here is a non-exhaustive list of people in the picture: Dave Ackley, Richard Durbin, Bart Selman, Dave Plaut, Bartlett Mel, Jim Anderson, Andy Barto, Richard Golden, Michael Mozer, Stanislas Dehaene, Mitsuo Kawato, Yves Chauvin, Yann LeCun, Jonathan Bachrach, Michael Jordan, Jim Hendler, David Willshaw, Dave Parker, Eric Saund, Charlie Rosenberg, Steve Nowlan, Dana Ballard, Dave Touretzky, Jay McClelland, Geoff Hinton, Terry Sejnowski.以上就是我的精选版人工智能发展史中与CMU相关的部分，可能有所疏漏，欢迎小伙伴们留言补充。——————————————————————————————————————下面我们来看一下CMU BSAI学位的课程设置。链接：Coming this Fall: B.S. in Artificial IntelligenceBSAI的课程设置几乎整合了校内现有的最好资源：数学、统计、计算机、（现有的）人工智能、科学、工程、人文学科。具体每一学期的必修和选修课程在下图中有说明。我简单看了一眼，感觉要念下来还是挺辛苦的。其他系我不是很熟，不过心理系的课我看了，都是非常相关的明星课程。BSAI majors will take courses in math and statistics, computer science, AI, science and engineering, and humanities and arts. There's also room built into the curriculum for academic exploration via electives. Here's how the curriculum breaks down.Math and Statistics Core (6 Courses)Math Foundations of Computer Science (15-151)Differential and Integral Calculus (21-120)Integration and Approximation (21-122)Matrices and Linear Transformations (21-241)Probability Theory for Computer Scientists (36-218)Modern Regression (36-401)Computer Science Core (5 Courses Plus Freshman Immigration Course)Freshman Immigration Course (15-128)Principles of Imperative Computation (15-122)Principles of Functional Programming (15-150)Parallel and Sequential Data Structures and Algorithms (15-210)Introduction to Computer Systems (15-213)Great Theoretical Ideas in Computer Science (15-251)Artificial Intelligence Core (3 Courses Plus Concepts in Artificial Intelligence)Concepts in Artificial Intelligence (Mini, Spring Semester)Introduction to AI Representation and Problem Solving (15-381)Introduction to Machine Learning (10-401)Take one of the following courses:Introduction to Natural Language Processing (11-411)Introduction to Computer Vision (16-385)Ethics Elective (1 Course From the Following)Freshman Seminar: Artificial Intelligence and Humanity (16-161)Ethics and Policy Issues in Computing (17-200)AI, Society and Humanity (80-249)AI Cluster Electives (4 Courses)Take one course from each of the following areas:Decision Making and Robotics ClusterNeural Computation (15-386)Truth, Justice and Algorithms (15-483)Cognitive Robotics (15-494)Strategic Reasoning for AI (new)Planning Techniques for Robotics (16-350)Mobile Robot Programming Laboratory (16-362)Robot Kinematics and Dynamics (16-384)Planning, Execution and Learning (new)Machine Learning ClusterDeep Reinforcement Learning and Control (10-403)Machine Learning for Text Mining (11-441)Advanced Data Analysis (36-402)Introduction to Deep Learning (new)Perception and Language ClusterSearch Engines (11-442)Speech Processing (11-492)Computational Perception (15-387)Computational Photography (15-463)Vision Sensors (16-421)Human-AI Interaction ClusterDesigning Human-Centered Systems (05-391)Human-Robot Interaction (16-467)Learning From People (new)Design Studio on Intelligent Products and Services (new)Humanities and ArtsBSAI students take seven courses in the humanities and arts as part of the SCS General Education requirements. Of the seven Humanities and Arts courses in the curriculum, one must be in cognitive science or cognitive psychology. Examples include:Cognitive Psychology (85-211)Human Information Processing and Artificial Intelligence (85-213)Perception (85-370)Human Memory (85-390)Visual Cognition (85-408)Cognitive Modeling (85-412)Language and Thought (85-421)Learning in Humans and Machines (85-426)Science and EngineeringBSAI students take four courses in science and engineering as part of the SCS General Education requirements.咦，你居然看到最后了。其实就想说，BSAI大概是曾经幼齿的我在大学最好的时光里最想要的知识体系构架吧。（笔芯～）暂时没有彩蛋唉，不过可能会不定期更新哦。一个虎头蛇尾的人首发于具有纪念意义的2018年5月10日